{
  "text": "Soft-to-hard deterministic annealing. Our soft assignment scheme gives us differentiable approximationsF andH(φ) of the discretized networkF and the sample entropy H(p), respectively. However, our objective is to learn network parameters W that minimize (6) when using the encoder and decoder with hard assignments, such that we obtain a compressible symbol stream E(z) which we can compress using, e.g., arithmetic coding [CITATION_1] .",
